Mr Sunday Akuns, a Chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party in Plateau State has said the party’s victory in the Saturday by-election signified more victories in coming elections for the party in the state. DAILY POST reports that Musa Agah a PDP lawmaker in the Plateau State House of Assembly was declared winner of the Jos North/Bassa Federal Constituency’s by-election on Sunday. The PDP chieftain, in a statement on Monday, said the party’s victory had revitalised hope and energy that the party would take over power in the state in 2023. He said, “It is time to close ranks, upgrade our strategies and ensure we remain very focused and highly committed toward greater achievements.” He commended the patriotic youths, women, other critical stakeholders, as well as leaders who moved in the hot sun and dust to champion the victory. He assured that they are just a few miles away from restoring the hope, dignity and confidence of the good people of the state. He added that the state under the leadership of the PDP government would ensure the security, welfare and economic prosperity of the people.